       Why are sea ice extent and area not available for Dec. 1987 and Jan. 1988? 






          Kara

          posted this on July 7, 2011, 13:18






          Question:  

 Why are sea ice extent and area not available for Dec. 1987 and Jan. 1988 

  Answer:  

 Those were two months when there was limited data. January had data for only about the 2nd half of the month and December had only a
few days of data. Thus monthly means produced from such sparse data would not be representative of the true monthly conditions. 

 Unfortunately there is not another good data source for those two months, particularly in Antarctica. Any other data source, other than from the SSM/I satellite would not be consistent enough to calculate a trend or to perform a variability analysis. A best estimate for total extent over the entire hemisphere could be obtained by linearly interpolating between November and February. If the monthly fields themselves are desired (i.e., the 2-D spatial grid of ice
concentration or extent), then it could be produced from the daily data, following guidelines in the  documentation . 

   



   

   










