       Where can I get archived sea ice images to add to a KML file? 






          Kara

          posted this on July 7, 2011, 13:20






          Question:  

 Where can I get archived sea ice images to add to to a KML file? 

  Answer:  

 The SSM/I images are archived  online .

 The AMSR images are higher resolution than the SSM/I and are also archived  online . The directory includes north, south, and global images in a cylindrical projections as well as polar stereo images that are not suitable for Google Earth, but may be better for other purposes. 

   












